-- Turkey's Bank Asya shares drop on uncertainty on its sale process
-- By Seda Sezer
-- Thu Aug 07, 2014 02:46AM EDT
-- None



ISTANBUL, Aug 7 (Reuters) - Shares of Turkey's Islamic lender Bank Asya tumbled on Thursday after conflicting statements from government officials over the bank's sale process confused investors.

Turkish Deputy Prime Minister Ali Babacan said on Wednesday that state-run Ziraat Bank could buy Bank Asya. [ID:nL6N0QC3MX] Yigit Bulut, an adviser to Tayyip Erdogan, said late on Wednesday the prime minister had no knowledge of plans for Ziraat to buy Bank Asya, denying Babacan's comments, Sabah newspaper reported.